<p>I start a new note for each chapter, and Iâ€™m writing everything in markdown. When I write something but I think it needs more rigor, I highlight the text to remind myself to revisit it. When I stop writing each morning, I add a comment at my last passage that simply says, â€œStopping point.â€ I do this because from time to time I end up writing out of sequence, so picking up where I left off is not as simple as scrolling to the end of a note.</p>

